Data Preparation:

dataSource = read_csv("DMv3c.csv")
names(dataSource)[1] = "Country"

Phase A: Conduct an empirical analysis on the effects of global economic development on environmental degradation as modeled by Gross National Income and CO2 Emissions on a per-capita basis. Find significant Kuznets Curve relationship between predictor and response variable

PA.Tested1:

#I: Conditions of Simple Linear Model (Model Linearity, Error Constant Variance, Error Zero Mean, Error Independence, Error Normality)

#Condition 1: Model Linearity & Condition 3: Error Constant Variance:
dataSourceTemp = subset(dataSource, !is.na(CO2_e_2009))
dataSourceTemp = subset(dataSource, !is.na(GNI_pc_2009))

lmod1 = lm(CO2_e_2009~GNI_pc_2009, data=dataSourceTemp)

plot(CO2_e_2009~GNI_pc_2009, data=dataSourceTemp)
abline(lmod1)


plot(lmod1, 1)


#Condition 2: Error Zero mean:
plot(lmod1$residuals~lmod1$fitted.values)
abline(a=0, b=0)


#Condition 4: Error Independence & #Conditions 5: Error Normal
hist(lmod1$residuals)

qqnorm(lmod1$residuals)
qqline(lmod1$residuals)


#II. Data Transformation & Second Order Polynomials

set.seed(9252020)
rows <- sample(nrow(dataSourceTemp)) 
dataSourceTemp = dataSourceTemp[rows,]
dTrain=dataSourceTemp[1:152,] #select the training sample 
dHoldout=dataSourceTemp[153:190,] #create the holdout sample

Full = lm(log(CO2_e_2009)~I(log(GNI_pc_2009)^2)+log(GNI_pc_2009), data=dTrain)
MSE = (summary(Full)$sigma)^2
none = lm(log(CO2_e_2009)~1, data=dTrain)

modelA = step(none, scope=list(upper=Full), scale=MSE, trace=TRUE)

#I. Shrinkage & Rudimentary Cross Validation by change in R^2

dataSourceTemp = subset(dataSource, !is.na(CO2_e_2014))
dataSourceTemp = subset(dataSource, !is.na(GNI_pc_2014))

modelB$coefficients[1:3] = c(B0, B1, B2)
